A. Data preparation

A.1. Data for main analysis

# calculate the sample size of studies with multiple groups (sum) or outcomes (max)
df.DT.Ngrp <- data.table::setDT(df)[, .(x = sum(N_tot)), by =.(First_author_meta, Year_meta, Intervention, author, year, Outcome_general, multiple_es, id_row)][, .(N_cor = max(x)), by=.(First_author_meta, Year_meta, Intervention, author, year, Outcome_general)]

# reinsert corrected sample size in the initial dataset
df.DT.preagg <- dplyr::left_join(df, df.DT.Ngrp, by = c("First_author_meta", "Year_meta", "Intervention", "author", "year", "Outcome_general"))

df.DT.preagg$included_meta <- as.numeric(as.character(df.DT.preagg$included_meta))

# aggregate dataset at the outcome level
dfagg <- df.DT.preagg[, lapply(.SD, function(x)
         weighted.mean(x, N_cor, na.rm = TRUE)), 
  by = c("First_author_meta", "Year_meta", "Intervention", "author", "year", "Outcome_general"), 
  .SDcols = c(# participants
              "MeanAge", "MeanIQ", "PercMale",
              # intervention - length
              "LengthWeek", "DurationMonth", 
              # intervention -implementer
              "parent_imp", "prof_imp", 
              # intervention -setting
              "sett_home", "sett_clin", "sett_class",
              # RoB
              "RCT_cat", "Detect_cat", "high_rob_cat",
              # outcome
              "Outcome_test", "Outcome_questionnaire", "Outcome_observation",
              "Active_controls",
              "included_meta")]

df1 <- dplyr::left_join(data.frame(dfagg), data.frame(df.DT.Ngrp))
## Joining, by = c("First_author_meta", "Year_meta", "Intervention", "author", "year", "Outcome_general")
# aggregate dataset at the meta-analysis level
df.tot <- data.table::setDT(df1)[, lapply(.SD, function(x)
  weighted.mean(x, N_cor, na.rm = TRUE)), 
  by = c("First_author_meta", "Year_meta", "Intervention", "Outcome_general", "included_meta"), 
  .SDcols =  c(# participants
              "MeanAge", "MeanIQ", "PercMale",
              # intervention - length
              "LengthWeek", "DurationMonth", 
              # intervention -implementer
              "parent_imp", "prof_imp", 
              # intervention -setting
              "sett_home", "sett_clin", "sett_class",
              # RoB
              "RCT_cat", "Detect_cat", "high_rob_cat",
              # outcome
              "Outcome_test", "Outcome_questionnaire", "Outcome_observation",
              "Active_controls",
              "included_meta")]

# create some new variables to facilitate data presentation
df.tot$factor <- with(df.tot, paste0(First_author_meta, "_", Intervention, "_", Outcome_general))

df.tot$Paper <- with(df.tot, paste0(First_author_meta, " (", Year_meta, ")"))

df.tot$LengthWeek_round <- round(df.tot$LengthWeek)
df.tot$Intensity <- with(df.tot,
      ifelse(LengthWeek < 2, "< 2 h/wk",
        ifelse(LengthWeek < 5, "2-4 h/wk",
          ifelse(LengthWeek < 10, "5-9 h/wk", 
           ifelse(LengthWeek < 20, "10-19 h/wk",
            ifelse(LengthWeek >= 20, ">= 20h/wk", NA_real_))))))

df.tot$Age <- with(df.tot,
      ifelse(MeanAge < 7, "< 7 yo",
        ifelse(MeanAge < 12, "7-11 yo",
          ifelse(MeanAge < 20, "12-19 yo", 
            ifelse(MeanAge >= 20, ">= 20 yo", NA_real_)))))

df.tot$IQ <- with(df.tot,
      ifelse(MeanIQ < 70, "Low (< 70)",
        ifelse(MeanIQ < 80, "Limit (70-79)",
          ifelse(MeanIQ < 120, "Average (80-119)", 
            ifelse(MeanIQ < 130, "High (120-129)", 
              ifelse(MeanIQ >= 130, "Very high (130+)",
                     NA_real_))))))

df.tot$Duration <- with(df.tot,
      ifelse(DurationMonth < 2, "< 2 months",
        ifelse(DurationMonth <= 6, "2-6 months",
        ifelse(DurationMonth <= 12, "7-12 months",
          ifelse(DurationMonth > 12, "> 12 months",
                 NA_real_)))))

A.2. Data for sensitivity analysis

# subset dataframe to RCTs with low risk of bias regarding blinding of outcome assessors
df.S1 <- subset(df, rob == "low")

# adjust for shared control group
df.S1$n_controls_adj <- df.S1$n_controls
df.S1[which(!is.na(df$shared_controls)), ]$n_controls_adj <- df.S1[which(!is.na(df$shared_controls)), ]$n_controls_adj / 2

# calculate adjusted total sample size
df.S1$N_tot <- apply(df.S1[, c('n_cases', 'n_controls_adj')], 1, sum)

# studies with multiple independent subgroups are identified with an unique id_row to facilitate aggregation
df.S1$id_row <- 1:nrow(df.S1)
df.S1[which(df.S1$multiple_es == "groups"), ]$id_row <- 9999

df.DT.Ngrp.S1 <- data.table::setDT(df.S1)[, .(x = sum(N_tot)), by =.(First_author_meta, Year_meta, Intervention, author, year, Outcome_general, multiple_es, id_row)][, .(N_cor = max(x)), by=.(First_author_meta, Year_meta, Intervention, author, year, Outcome_general)]

B. Main analysis

B.1. Data analysis

res.transit <- summary(add.evidence(umbrella(df, mult.level = TRUE), criteria = "Ioannidis_umb"))
## Warning in .check_data(x): Some warnings occurred. Please verify warning
## messages shown.
res <- gen_id(res.transit)

res$factor <- with(res, paste0(Author, "_", intervention, "_", Outcome))

res.main <- merge(res, df.tot, by = "factor")
res.main$Sample_size_studies <- with(res.main, paste0(N, " (", Stud, ")"))
res.main$Effect_size <- with(res.main, paste0("SMD = ", Value, " [", CI_lo, "-", CI_up, "]"))

res.main$Risk_of_bias <- with(res.main,
      ifelse(rob < 50, "High", # (>= 50% studies)
        ifelse(rob < 75, "Med.", # (25-50 % studies)
          ifelse(rob >= 75, "Low", # (< 25% studies)
                 NA_real_))))

res.main$se <- with(res.main, (CI_up - CI_lo) / 3.92)
res.main$Setting <- NA
for (i in 1:nrow(res.main)) {
  if (!is.nan(res.main$sett_home[i]) | 
      !is.nan(res.main$sett_clin[i]) |
      !is.nan(res.main$sett_class[i])) {
    res.main$Setting[i] <- c("Home", "Clinic", "Classroom")[which.max(c(res.main$sett_home[i], res.main$sett_clin[i], res.main$sett_class[i]))]
  } else {
    res.main$Setting[i] <- NA
  }
}
    
res.main$Implementer <- NA
for (i in 1:nrow(res.main)) {
  if (!is.nan(res.main$prof_imp[i]) | 
      !is.nan(res.main$parent_imp[i])) {
    res.main$Implementer[i] <- c("Profesionnal", "Caregiver")[which.max(c(res.main$prof_imp[i], res.main$parent_imp[i]))]
  } else {
    res.main$Implementer[i] <- NA
  }
}
  
  
res.main$Type_of_outcome <- NA
for (i in 1:nrow(res.main)) {
  if (!is.nan(res.main$Outcome_test[i]) | 
      !is.nan(res.main$Outcome_questionnaire[i]) |
      !is.nan(res.main$Outcome_observation[i])) {
    res.main$Type_of_outcome[i] <- c("Test", "Reporting", "Observation")[which.max(c(res.main$Outcome_test[i], res.main$Outcome_questionnaire[i], res.main$Outcome_observation[i]))]
  } else {
    res.main$Type_of_outcome[i] <- NA
  }
}

# res.main$Intervention <- gsub("\\s*\\([^\\)]+\\)","", res.main$Intervention)

res.main$Active_controls <- paste0(round(res.main$Active_controls), "%")
display.cols <- c("Paper", "Intervention", "Outcome", "Class", 'Sample size (studies)',

                  'Effect size', "p.value", "PI", "I2", "Egger_p",

                  "N", "Value", 
                  "included_meta", "se")

interv <- c("EIBI", "NDBI", "DEV", "PMI", "SSG", "TEACCH", "CBT", "TECH")
mainsympt <- c("Overall ASD symptoms", "Social communication", "Repetitive behaviors", "Adaptive behaviors", "Cognition(IQ)", "Language(Exp)", "Language(Recep)", "Problematic behaviors")

ASDsympt <- c("Overall ASD symptoms", "Social communication", "Repetitive behaviors")

  paste0("The number of meta-analyses associated with a weak evidence rating is equal to: ", nrow(subset(res.main, included_meta == 1 & Class == "IV")), " (", round(nrow(subset(res.main, included_meta == 1 & Class == "IV")) / nrow(subset(res.main, included_meta == 1)), 2)*100, "%)", ". "),
  
  paste0("The number of meta-analyses associated with a non-significant rating is equal to: ", nrow(subset(res.main, included_meta == 1 & Class == "ns")), " (", round(nrow(subset(res.main, included_meta == 1 & Class == "ns")) / nrow(subset(res.main, included_meta == 1)), 2)*100, "%)", ". ")
)

The number of meta-analyses associated with a non-significant rating is equal to: 23 (50%). "

C. Sensitivity analysis

C.1. Low RoB

Data analysis

res.transit.S1.1 <- summary(add.evidence(umbrella(df.S1, mult.level = TRUE), criteria = "Ioannidis_umb")); res.transit.S1 <- gen_id(res.transit.S1.1)

res.transit.S1$factor <- with(res.transit.S1, paste0(Author, "_", intervention, "_", Outcome))

res.S1 <- merge(res.transit.S1, df.tot.S1, by = "factor")
res.S1$Sample_size_studies <- with(res.S1, paste0(N, " (", Stud, ")"))
res.S1$Effect_size <- with(res.S1, paste0("SMD = ", Value, " [", CI_lo, "-", CI_up, "]"))
res.S1$se <- with(res.S1, (CI_up - CI_lo) / 3.92)

res.S1$Risk_of_bias <- with(res.S1,
      ifelse(rob <= 50, "High", # (>= 50% studies)
        ifelse(rob <= 75, "Moderate", # (25-50 % studies)
          ifelse(rob > 75, "Low", # (< 25% studies)
                 NA_real_))))

res.S1$Setting <- NA
for (i in 1:nrow(res.S1)) {
  if (!is.nan(res.S1$sett_home[i]) | 
      !is.nan(res.S1$sett_clin[i]) |
      !is.nan(res.S1$sett_class[i])) {
    res.S1$Setting[i] <- c("Home", "Clinic", "Classroom")[which.max(c(res.S1$sett_home[i], res.S1$sett_clin[i], res.S1$sett_class[i]))]
  } else {
    res.S1$Setting[i] <- NA
  }
}
    
res.S1$Implementer <- NA
for (i in 1:nrow(res.S1)) {
  if (!is.nan(res.S1$prof_imp[i]) | 
      !is.nan(res.S1$parent_imp[i])) {
    res.S1$Implementer[i] <- c("Profesionnal", "Caregiver")[which.max(c(res.S1$prof_imp[i], res.S1$parent_imp[i]))]
  } else {
    res.S1$Implementer[i] <- NA
  }
}
  
  
res.S1$Type_of_outcome <- NA
for (i in 1:nrow(res.S1)) {
  if (!is.nan(res.S1$Outcome_test[i]) | 
      !is.nan(res.S1$Outcome_questionnaire[i]) |
      !is.nan(res.S1$Outcome_observation[i])) {
    res.S1$Type_of_outcome[i] <- c("Test", "Reporting", "Observation")[which.max(c(res.S1$Outcome_test[i], res.S1$Outcome_questionnaire[i], res.S1$Outcome_observation[i]))]
  } else {
    res.S1$Type_of_outcome[i] <- NA
  }
}

res.S1$Intervention <- gsub("\\s*\\([^\\)]+\\)","", res.S1$Intervention)
